                            <comment id="19335" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2011 06:56:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch is available:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1252&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1252&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19331" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2011 03:17:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the target user only belong to one group, then we just set &quot;identity-&amp;gt;mi_gid&quot;, and does not set &quot;identity-&amp;gt;mi_ginfo&quot;, then save the memory allocation and unnecessary groups processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So here, we miss to check whether &quot;identity-&amp;gt;mi_ginfo&quot; is valid, just access &quot;identity-&amp;gt;mi_ginfo-&amp;gt;ngroups&quot; directly, so caused invalide memory accessing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19295" author="green" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2011 12:41:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also looked at it a bit and I cannot reproduce any problems when I try to access 2.1 servers from 1.8 client as non-root.&lt;br/&gt;
I only did simple accesses like touch, cat and such, though.&lt;br/&gt;
If anything more complicated is required, please specify the exact reproduction steps.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19282" author="pjones" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2011 10:01:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hongchao will look into this one&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19279" author="yujian" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2011 09:10:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue blocks all of the tests which need to be run by non-root users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
